cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.SY 

This paper is about a machine learning training method, specifically a framework for Population Based Training (PBT). The paper discusses the optimization of neural network weights and hyperparameters, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of dynamic hyperparameter schedules and the application of the PBT system to a generative model also suggest relevance to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the coordination of asynchronous trials across a cluster and the general, black-box design of the framework may also be of interest to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
